&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Classic Russian cuisine from the&nbsp;classic Russian novel&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Oblomov&lt;/em&gt; is located in Zamoskvorechye, an old quarter of Moscow where 18th- and 19th-century estates are preserved. Our company completely restored a former merchant&amp;#8217;s residence that is now home to the restaurant. The mercantile furnishings of the restaurant have the feel of theatrical decorations &ndash; Oblomov is the place where you forget about time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Indeed, genuine mercantile furnishings are a very rare sight in modern day Moscow. The decorations &ndash; old knick-knacks, furniture and curios, including sideboards, pictures in heavy frames, ornate mirrors, chests of drawers and even an old typewriter &ndash; were collected across Russia and then lovingly restored.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Guests can choose a table on one of three floors. Awaiting you on the first, is a charming coffee house serving divine coffee which we roast ourselves. The second floor is divided into two rooms &amp;#8211; Shtolz and Oblomov, where Russian and European dishes are served. On the third floor is the Eastern Room, where guests can smoke hookahs, read and play cards. A summer garden is always open during the warmer months of the year &ndash; we offer dishes cooked on a traditional Russian barbecue and in an authentic Russian stove.&lt;/p&gt;
